reviewText: Low budget but good cheerleaders fight back with chainsaws against a evil witch. It's not the best movie ever made but it's good I got a autograph copy from Jackie hall who stars in the film and she's a hottie.

when i first went looking for this film, i had heard about a nearly 2 hr version of it and did find a place which had it, but no cover-art and other problems, so i decided to settle for this one. this film has tiffany shepis and a few other actress' whom have gone on to much better films and one even got into the country music genre, which i just don't understand these days. the acting is "get your lines right and we have a take". special effect's are decent but there seems to be some sort of storyline plot-holes throu-out this film, which makes it seem to lack in
"impact" especially when the demon process transformation is taking place, which means to me this version of the film was chopped-down most likely for time-constraints or to reduce fear factor or maybe the deletion of some supposed "occult" scenes. if this is the case and this is the "covert" censored version, then i say, buy it if you want, but i am currently considering giving my copy away if i cannot find the rumored X-rated original.

the only reason why i compare this to fred olen ray's hollywood chainsaw hookers is because his film is so cheesy and cartoonishly funny and this one underhandedly arrogant, i have yet to watch this again, since i bought it.
One of the strangers and cheapest, cheesiest movies I've ever watched and I didn't even make it to the end.

Hands down, CHAINSAW CHEERLEADERS is my all-time favorite Tiffany Shepis movie. Playing a sassy witch who tangles with cheerleaders, Tiffany is always great to watch. I watched this movie at least three times in one week!!!
